.TH "Element.toggleAttribute" "JS" "February 15, 2024" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
Element.toggleAttribute \- Element: toggleAttribute() method
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]toggleAttribute()\f[B]\f[R] method of the
\f[CR]Element\f[R] interface toggles a Boolean attribute (removing it if
it is present and adding it if it is not present) on the given element.
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
toggleAttribute(name)
toggleAttribute(name, force)
.EE
.SS Parameters
.TP
\f[B]name\f[R]
A string specifying the name of the attribute to be toggled.
The attribute name is automatically converted to all lower\-case when
\f[CR]toggleAttribute()\f[R] is called on an HTML element in an HTML
document.
.TP
\f[B]force\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
A boolean value which has the following effects:
.RS
.IP \[bu] 2
if not specified at all, the \f[CR]toggleAttribute\f[R] method
\[lq]toggles\[rq] the attribute named \f[CR]name\f[R] \[em] removing it
if it is present, or else adding it if it is not present
.IP \[bu] 2
if true, the \f[CR]toggleAttribute\f[R] method adds an attribute named
\f[CR]name\f[R]
.IP \[bu] 2
if false, the \f[CR]toggleAttribute\f[R] method removes the attribute
named \f[CR]name\f[R]
.RE
.SS Return value
\f[CR]true\f[R] if attribute \f[B]\f[CB]name\f[B]\f[R] is eventually
present, and \f[CR]false\f[R] otherwise.
.SS Exceptions
.TP
\f[B]InvalidCharacterError\f[R] \f[B]DOMException\f[R]
The specified attribute \f[CR]name\f[R] contains one or more characters
which are not valid in attribute names.
.SH EXAMPLES
In the following example, \f[CR]toggleAttribute()\f[R] is used to toggle
the \f[CR]disabled\f[R] attribute of an \f[CR]<input>\f[R].
.SS HTML
.IP
.EX
<\f[B]input\f[R] value=\[dq]text\[dq] /> <\f[B]button\f[R]>toggleAttribute(\[dq]disabled\[dq])</\f[B]button\f[R]>
.EE
.SS JavaScript
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] button = document.querySelector(\[dq]button\[dq]);
\f[B]const\f[R] input = document.querySelector(\[dq]input\[dq]);

button.addEventListener(\[dq]click\[dq], () \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  input.toggleAttribute(\[dq]disabled\[dq]);
});
.EE
